    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Electronic keyboard instruments designed to imitate the tone of conventional pipe organs, and, like pipe organs, are able to sustain the tone indefinitely, play chords, and decrease or increase sustained tone.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Instrumentos de teclado electrónicos diseñados para imitar el tono de los órganos convencionales de tubo y, al igual que los órganos de tubo, son capaces de prolongar el tono indefinidamente, tocar acordes, y bajar o subir el tono sostenido.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Orgels die langs elektronische weg het geluid van traditionele pijporgels imiteren.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
